div.p:
               I should like to ask you particularly, dear friend, to send me the address of your wife's parents, as I should like to call on the lady during her visit here and pay her my respects.

Mary Haast had a severe nervous breakdown following the birth of her fourth son, Julius Hermann Haast, in December 1873 (H. F. von Haast (1948), p. 682
                     ), and went to stay with her parents in Victoria, where her father, Edward Dobson, was engineer for the construction of the Geelong Waterworks. She arrived in Melbourne aboard Otago on 28 October 1874 (Argus, 29 October 1874, p. 4).
